In late 1994 Rudd, together with Sarah McLeod (ex-Fallen Down Monster) (lead vocals, guitar), Paul Berryman (drums) and Chris Tennent (lead guitar) formed Hell's Kitchen in Adelaide.
Rudd and Tennent had been jamming together for about a year before Rudd tried out for McLeod's latest band.

Jet Age was nominated at the 2001 ARIA Music Awards, for Best Rock Album and Best Cover Art.

In June 2004 the Superjesus split following their 'Rock Music' tour.
